State MSM Profile: Arizona

Background & Methods

In 2015-2016, researchers at Emory University partnered with colleagues at the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) to develop methods to estimate the number of men who have sex with men (MSM) residing in each county in the United States. Using population and housing data from the American Community Survey and estimates from two peer-reviewed publications (Oster et al., 2015 & Purcell et al., 2012), they derived an indirect estimate of MSM population sizes that took into account both the urbanicity of the county as well as its density of households with a male householder and a male same-sex partner.

The full methodology is published in the Journal of Medical Internet Research - Public Health and Surveillance:

Grey JA, Bernstein KT, Sullivan PS, Purcell DW, Chesson HW, Gift TL, Rosenberg ES. Estimating the population sizes of men who have sex with men in US states and counties using data from the American Community Survey. JMIR Public Health Surveill 2016;2(1):e14. DOI: 10.2196/publichealth.5365

Overview of MSM in Arizona

An estimated 110,343 men who have sex with men (MSM) resided in Arizona in 2013, representing 2.5% of the 4,503,084 MSM in the United States. Of the 2,393,283 adult men of Arizona, 4.6% had had sex with another man in the past 5 years, which was greater than the overall percentage of adult men in the United States who were MSM (3.9%).

Most MSM in Arizona resided in central counties of large metropolitan areas (79.7%). Including both central and fringe counties, 84.1% resided in a large metropolitan area.


Percentage of MSM by urbanicity, United States and Arizona, 2013

MSM in Arizona Counties

Among counties or county-equivalent areas in Arizona, Maricopa County had the largest population of MSM at 87,893, representing 79.7% of all MSM in the state. Maricopa County also had the highest percentage of MSM among adult men in Arizona at 6.2%. This was greater than the percentage for Arizona as a whole, which was 4.6% of adult men.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.



MSM in Arizona Metropolitan Statistical Areas

Phoenix-Mesa-Scottsdale Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Phoenix-Mesa-Scottsdale MSA had the largest metropolitan population of MSM in Arizona at 92,825, or 84.1% of all MSM in the state. Of the 1,557,094 adult men in Phoenix-Mesa-Scottsdale, an estimated 6.0% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.




Tucson Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Tucson MSA had a population of 10,238 MSM, or 9.3% of all MSM in Arizona. Of the 371,308 adult men in Tucson, an estimated 2.8% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.




Prescott Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Prescott MSA had a population of 1,467 MSM, or 1.3% of all MSM in Arizona. Of the 83,457 adult men in Prescott, an estimated 1.8% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.




Yuma Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Yuma MSA had a population of 1,241 MSM, or 1.1% of all MSM in Arizona. Of the 73,266 adult men in Yuma, an estimated 1.7% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.




Sierra Vista-Douglas Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Sierra Vista-Douglas MSA had a population of 1,218 MSM, or 1.1% of all MSM in Arizona. Of the 51,600 adult men in Sierra Vista-Douglas, an estimated 2.4% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.




Lake Havasu City-Kingman Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Lake Havasu City-Kingman MSA had a population of 1,190 MSM, or 1.1% of all MSM in Arizona. Of the 80,695 adult men in Lake Havasu City-Kingman, an estimated 1.5% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.




Flagstaff Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Flagstaff MSA had a population of 901 MSM, or 0.8% of all MSM in Arizona. Of the 50,728 adult men in Flagstaff, an estimated 1.8% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.
